I've gotta say, you know, in my personal seeming appearance of experience, and things like that:  starting to have some kindness come out again, after I was pretty angry and everything; that's, to me, the true miracle, right?  There's a lot of other stuff that comes with this, that I didn't expect, but, just finding some peace, and confidence in the ineffable, confidence without cause, peace without cause, without any intoxications, without bodily comforts, even...

You know, that's why we're very lucky to have people like Rolpa presenting so openly their experiences, like, presenting their challenges, and still finding this great peace.  To me, that's truly miraculous.  Why this is working for people, right?  We just  present it for them, in the most skillful way we can, and they get some freedom.  

And you-all can do that for each other, right?  Once we get to a point where we're confident enough, or maybe we're just excited, we're talking about it, we can really have that butterfly effect.  As long as we're dealing with authentic practice, we're being honest with ourselves and others, we're not just psychoanalyzing, projecting onto others and things like that---it's like lending a hand when somebody slipped and fell, or something like that.  It's gotta be authentic from the heart, spontaneous, unplanned, uncontrived.  We don't want to "help" people (in air quotes), overly help people right?  We don't want to proselytize; that wouldn't be according to Dzogchen tradition, anyway.  And so like that, it can have a tremendous effect on the collective, to just have this awareness practice. 
